text:
Is anyone else pulling their hair out about HubSpot emails in Outlook? Looks like they changed some default code underlying all email templates and didn’t tell anyone. It’s not breaking emails in Outlook and NOT rendering in Litmus checks BEFORE we send them.

I notice 3 things have changed that may haver something to do with it but I’m fairly certain it’s the last one:

• There is an added ‘height=“auto”’ attribute added to all images. 
• All of their drag-and-drop sections have a div element with a class “hse-column-container” that no longer have an inline “width: 100%;” attribute.
• Most importantly there is a major change to an if statement immediately after this element that is specifically related to Outlook:
